5. Save the script by clicking the "File" menu and selecting "Save."
6. Refresh the web page where you want the script to run.

After completing these steps, your script should be functioning in a user script context and will be installed as a Tampermonkey user script. Note that the `@grant` directive in the header information is necessary to grant Tampermonkey permission to run the `GM_setClipboard` function.

