This code sets some styles for the menu element selected by the `querySelector` method. The styles include: a background color of `#333`, a padding of `10px`, a text color of `white`, a display of `flex`, justification of the contents within the element to be `space-between`, alignment of the contents within the element to be `center`, and removal of the default list style.

You can use `display: flex` and `flex-wrap: wrap` properties in the parent div and set a width for the child elements, then add `justify-content: space-between` or `justify-content: space-around` to add the desired padding between the elements.

